
INTRODUCTION

This project focuses on developing digital literacy skills required for students in today’s digital world. It covers online presence, communication, collaboration tools, and cybersecurity awareness.

TASK 1

I created my digital literacy awareness infographic using Canva, as it offers a wide range of customizable templates and an intuitive interface suitable for beginners. The infographic focuses on key aspects of digital literacy such as safe internet practices, useful digital tools for students, and maintaining a professional online presence.

In the design, I included important points like creating strong passwords, identifying suspicious links, and using platforms such as GitHub and LinkedIn to build a professional profile. I used icons, contrasting colors, and short bullet points to make the content visually appealing and easy to understand at a glance. The goal was to ensure that even someone with minimal prior knowledge could quickly grasp the importance of digital literacy.

One of the main challenges I faced was balancing the amount of information with the visual layout. It was difficult to decide what to include without overcrowding the infographic. However, this process helped me understand how to prioritize key information and present it effectively. Overall, this task improved both my digital awareness and my ability to communicate information visually.

TASK 2

For this task, I created and updated my profiles on GitHub and LinkedIn to establish a professional digital presence. GitHub is primarily used for showcasing projects, managing code, and collaborating with others, making it an essential platform for students in technical fields. I created a profile README that includes my name, academic details, and a brief description of my learning goals.

On LinkedIn, I added my education details, including my current degree, institution, and expected graduation year. LinkedIn serves as a professional networking platform where students can connect with peers, seniors, and industry professionals, as well as explore internship and job opportunities.

These platforms will play an important role in my academic and professional journey over the next four years. I plan to regularly update my GitHub with projects and assignments, while using LinkedIn to build connections and stay informed about industry trends. This task helped me understand the importance of maintaining a clean and professional online presence from an early stage.

TASK 3

In this task, I explored both coding practice platforms and collaboration tools. I used HackerRank to complete a beginner-level coding challenge, which helped me understand basic problem-solving concepts and how coding platforms evaluate solutions. It was a good introduction to competitive programming and logical thinking.

Additionally, I created a Google Form as a Digital Literacy Awareness Quiz for my batchmates. The form includes five questions, combining multiple-choice and short-answer formats to test basic understanding of digital literacy concepts. I also reviewed the response section linked to Google Sheets, which demonstrates how data can be collected and analyzed efficiently.

These tools are highly useful in an academic environment. Platforms like HackerRank help improve coding skills and prepare students for technical interviews, while Google Forms and Sheets support collaboration, surveys, and data organization. Through this task, I gained practical experience in using these tools and understood how they can enhance both learning and teamwork.

TASK 4

This task helped me understand the importance of professional communication in academic and professional settings. Writing structured emails with clear subject lines, proper greetings, and polite language is essential to convey messages effectively.

Poor digital communication can lead to misunderstandings or missed opportunities. For example, if a student sends an email without a clear subject or uses informal language, it may be ignored or not taken seriously. This can result in delays or negative impressions.

By following proper email etiquette, such as being concise, respectful, and clear, these issues can be avoided. This task improved my ability to communicate professionally and made me more aware of how digital communication impacts others.

TASK 5

While researching cybercrime, I was surprised by how common and convincing phishing attacks have become. Many scams closely resemble legitimate messages, making it difficult for users to identify them. This highlights the importance of awareness and caution while using digital platforms.

One key learning from this task is the importance of verifying links and not sharing sensitive information such as passwords or OTPs. Even a small mistake can lead to serious consequences like financial loss or identity theft.

As a result, I will be more careful while interacting with emails and online messages, especially those requesting personal or financial information. This task has made me more responsible and aware of safe online practices.

CONCLUSION

This project provided valuable insights into digital literacy and its importance in today’s world. It helped me understand how to build a professional online presence, communicate effectively, use digital tools for learning, and stay safe online. Each task contributed to developing practical skills that will be useful throughout my academic and professional journey. Overall, this project has improved my awareness, confidence, and ability to use digital platforms responsibly.
